---
title: Puerto Rican-Style Beef & Sazón Spaghetti with Red Sauce, Bell Pepper & Onion
description: To celebrate la cultura this Hispanic Heritage Month, whip up this pasta dish that’s popular in Puerto Rico and the Dominican Republic! You’ll sauté and simmer up a sauce of onion and bell pepper with ground beef, zesty sazón seasoning (with cumin and achiote), and crushed tomatoes. Toss with spaghetti for a delicious spin on classic flavors.

image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/66ba48aafb4859096c8b628c-7008c12d.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/66ba48aafb4859096c8b628c-en-US.pdf
cuisine: Caribbean
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 790 kcal
  fat: 32 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 82 g
  sugar: 16 g
  protein: 37 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 730 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/puerto-rican-style-beef-and-sazon-spaghetti-66ba48aafb4859096c8b628c
author: Sara Heilman
course: main course
time required: 25 minutes
---

Bring a large #pot{} of water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and dice @onion{1} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Halve, core, and dice @green bell pepper{1} into 1⁄2-inch pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add onion and bell pepper; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until beginning to soften, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @ground beef{10%ounce} and @Loisa Sazón Organic Seasoning{1} to pan with veggies; season with salt and pepper. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> Carefully drain any excess grease from pan.

Stir in @crushed tomatoes{1%13.76oz can} and @sugar{1/4%teaspoon}. Bring to a simmer and cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce has thickened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, once water is boiling, add @spaghetti{6%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until just al dente, ~{8-10%minutes} (pasta will finish cooking in Step 5).

Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water (11⁄2 cups for 4 servings), then drain.

Add drained spaghetti and 1⁄2 cup reserved pasta cooking water (3⁄4 cup for 4 servings) to pan with sauce. Cook, stirring, until pasta is evenly coated, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> If needed, stir in additional reserved pasta cooking water a splash at a time until
> spaghetti is coated in sauce.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Divide pasta between #bowls{} and serve.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.